This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Moon of South Korea and President Trump of the United States during a meeting at the Blue House in Seoul. President Moon expressed gratitude for President Trump's visit and emphasized the hope for peace on the Korean Peninsula. President Trump thanked President Moon for their friendship and praised the business leaders of South Korea. He also mentioned the progress made in the relationship between North Korea and South Korea during his presidency. President Trump mentioned the possibility of meeting with Kim Jong Un and expressed pride in the accomplishments made in the region.